						               													<description>There is Estonian map on the game board with 10 cities and 2 crime-scenes per city.&amp;#10;The cards have city on the upper part of the card and evidence on bottom part of the card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Player move around board and make actions according to their character.&amp;#10;If criminal plays a card with the city he stands, he makes a crime to this city and draws one face-down evidence tile (footprint, fingerprint, dna, witness) to avaialable crime-scene of that city. Detective may visit that crime-scene and may turn the tile face-up by playing a card with that city. If criminal has 3 or more face-up evidences, detective may catch him and improson by playing 3 cards matching with the evidences of that criminal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Objective for criminals is to make 8 crimes to win.&amp;#10;Objective for detectives is to investigate crime-scenes, gather enough evidences and catch all criminals to win.&amp;#10;With combinations players may remove or add evidence-tiles to crime-scenes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Both character-types may deal and exchange cards with their partners.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     game board&amp;#10;     8 character cards&amp;#10;     55 action cards&amp;#10;     32 evidence tiles&amp;#10;     32 crime tokens in 4 colors&amp;#10;     4 criminals in 4 colors&amp;#10;     4 detectives in 4 colors&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
